social_posts.post_text:
An old favorite - the tunnel on film! It’s a great time any time of the day and with any film. Here, Christian (@cbshoots) took this with his Canon AE-1, a 50mm f/1.4 with some Kodak Portra 400. 

Have you taken a shot of the tunnel at Yosemite? Tag us!

Make sure to follow us at @YosemiteonFilm and use #yosemiteonfilm for a chance to be featured!

#madewithkodak #kodak #kodakportra400 #portra400 #filmisntdead #yosemite #yosemitenp

Happy New Year! 

I started the year off shooting some dense fog in the swamp. I haven’t in a long time, but I chose to go with black and white for these shots. These were some of my favorites.
allowing people and things to flow in and out of my life. I’m just along for the ride.

I explored the New Orleans area with @reecemerryman today. I’ve been having fun shooting with my @fujifilmx_us. A new workflow is nice. 

Big shoutout to @prismlensfx for the starburst and dream fx filters
Back at it with black and white swamp shot. This shot was from yet another foggy sunrise at Lake Martin. It’s been fun exploring this area. Louisiana has its moments for sure.

One thing I’ve always remembered about Louisiana from my childhood were the huge flocks of migrating birds that would come for the winter time. This moment definitely brought me way back. It felt cool to capture it #fujifilm
early stroll through the French Quarter  #myfujifilmlegacy
Louisiana just looks better in black and white #fujifilm
A stroll through the French Quarter #fujifilm

Scenes of Louisiana. #fujifilm
